description:
Nightmares & Fairy Tales follows the story of a doll called Annabelle and the people she comes in contact with.
The series was created by writer Serena Valentino and artist FSC. FSC left the series after 12 issues and was replaced by Crab Scrambly and then Camilla D'Errico.
After 8 years and several scheduling delays, the series ceased publication with 23 issues.

In 2010 the original team of Valentino and FSC began a new miniseries, but only published one issue was published before the project went on indefinite hiatus.

Collected Editions:

Nightmares & Fairy Tales

See Also:

Nightmares & Fairy Tales: Annabelle's Story
name: Nightmares & Fairy Tales

description: Lady Penelope was a British weekly comic for girls which ran from 1966 to 1969. The sister publication to TV Century 21, it was titled for its star, International Rescues' London agent Lady Penelope Creighton-Ward, from Gerry Anderson's Thunderbirds. Running alongside Lady Penelope's strip were strips featuring the Angels from Captain Scarlet and Marina from Stingray, both other Gerry Anderson shows, as well as strips based on US TV shows The Beverly Hillbillies, The Man from U.N.C.L.E., Bewitched and The Monkees. The first issue was dated 22 January 1966. The title changed to The New Lady Penelope with issue 53, back to Lady Penelope with issue 63 and then to Penelope from issue 123 onwards, as the comic dropped its connection to Gerry Anderson's shows. The run ended with issue 204, dated 13 December 1969, after which the title joined with Princess Tina.
name: Lady Penelope

description: Born  Born from the fire of his father and the passion of his mother, Antonio Valor, forged a commitment to bringing a new justice to Big City.  Brotherman: Dictator of Discipline is the continuing story of a man drawn deeper into the darkness to bring light to those who have lost all hope.  Armed only with his strength, wit, intellect, and his drive, Antonio Valor, straddles the line of being both the keeper and dispenser of the law.  Supported by a sprinkling of friends, colleagues, and confidants, the residents of Big City can begin to find peace in a place under siege. As it is written on the subway walls, “He’s here…and everything’s gonna be alright!”
name: Brotherman
